The paper deals with game theory and mechanism design, which are central topics in computer science. The focus on auctions and revenue maximization suggests that the paper could belong to cs.GT (Game Theory) or cs.EC (Economics and Computation). The use of dynamic approaches and repeated settings suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's use of axiomatic approaches and guarantees suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
